---
// src/pages/gitanjali.astro
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Gitanjali | God Is The Only Reality</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Plus+Jakarta+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 24 24' fill='%23ca9f1b'><path d='M12,22C12,22 4,16 4,12C4,8 12,2 12,2C12,2 20,8 20,12C20,16 12,22 12,22M12,4C12,4 7,8.5 7,12C7,15.5 12,19 12,19C12,19 17,15.5 17,12C17,8.5 12,4 12,4Z'/></svg>">
    <style is:global>
        :root {
            --bg: #030303;
            --text-main: #f3f4f6;
            --accent: #ca9f1b;
            --card-bg: rgba(14, 14, 14, 0.8);
            --card-border: rgba(214, 175, 55, 0.15);
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            background-color: var(--bg);
            color: var(--text-main);
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 5.5rem 2rem 4rem 2rem;
        }

        .bg-image {
            position: fixed;
            top: 0; 
            left: 0; 
            width: 100%; 
            height: 100%;
            /* Update the filename to match the large Tagore painting */
            background-image: url('/Tagore-painting-large.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center 20%;
            z-index: -1;
            /* Adjusted filters for the B&W painting to ensure text pops */
            filter: brightness(0.2) contrast(1.1) blur(4px);
            transition: filter 1s ease;
        }

        .content-container {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
            border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
            border-radius: 1.5rem;
            padding: 4rem;
            max-width: 850px;
            width: 100%;
        }

        .back-btn {
            position: fixed; top: 1.5rem; left: 1.5rem;
            z-index: 999; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
            background: rgba(14, 14, 14, 0.8);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            backdrop-filter: blur(20px); padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem; border-radius: 100px;
            color: var(--text-main); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s;
        }

        .back-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); transform: translateX(4px); }

        h1 {
            color: var(--accent);
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            margin-bottom: 4rem;
        }

        .chapter { margin-bottom: 4rem; }
        .chapter-title {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            color: var(--accent);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            display: block;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(202, 159, 27, 0.2);
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
            width: fit-content;
        }

        .poem-text {
            line-height: 1.8;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: rgba(243, 244, 246, 0.95);
            white-space: pre-wrap;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .content-container { padding: 2rem; }
            h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="bg-image"></div>
    <a href="/" class="back-btn">← Back</a>
    
    <div class="content-container">
        <h1>Gitanjali</h1>

        <div class="chapter">
            <span class="chapter-title">Chapter 1</span>
            <div class="poem-text">Thou hast made me endless, such is thy pleasure. This frail vessel thou emptiest again and again, and fillest it ever with fresh life.

This little flute of a reed thou hast carried over hills and dales, and hast breathed through it melodies eternally new.

At the immortal touch of thy hands my little heart loses its limits in joy and gives birth to utterance ineffable.

Thy infinite gifts come to me only on these very small hands of mine. Ages pass, and still thou pourest, and still there is room to fill.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter">
            <span class="chapter-title">Chapter 2</span>
            <div class="poem-text">When thou commandest me to sing it seems that my heart would break with pride; and I look to thy face, and tears come to my eyes.

All that is harsh and dissonant in my life melts into one sweet harmony - and my adoration spreads wings like a glad bird on its flight across the sea.

I know thou takest pleasure in my singing. I know that only as a singer I come before thy presence.

I touch by the edge of the far-spreading wing of my song thy feet which I could never aspire to reach.

Drunk with the joy of singing I forget myself and call thee friend who art my lord.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter">
            <span class="chapter-title">Chapter 103</span>
            <div class="poem-text">In one salutation to thee, my God, let all my senses spread out and touch this world at thy feet.

Like a rain-cloud of July hung low with its burden of unshed showers let all my mind bend down at thy door in one salutation to thee.

Let all my songs gather together their diverse strains into a single current and flow to a sea of silence in one salutation to thee.

Like a flock of homesick cranes flying night and day back to their mountain nests let all my life take its voyage to its eternal home in one salutation to thee.</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>